cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper deals with modeling the vehicle environment using lidar measurements and recurrent neural networks. The use of lidar measurements and neural networks suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new neural network architecture, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with motion estimation in dynamic occupancy grid maps, which is relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
